Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: An American system of directing traffic at street intersections, known as "the silent policeman," is to be given a trial by the Hamilton Borough Council.   At a recent meeting Mr H. H. Howden, who has just returned from America, said that domes, about five inches high and 15 inches in diameter, were used in the principal cities of America as a guide to those likely to cut the corner.
